	<td class="alt1" valign="top">
	
	<!-- message -->
	<p>I harbor no illusions that even one of these will get implemented. So without further ado:<br />
<br />
************************************************<br />
<br />
1) Fix Guk targetting. There is nothing more frustrating than the inability to click on MOBs to target.  This is semi-componded on multi-pulls and semi-solved with the cycle ability.  But there are times you want to click on a distant MOB to root it and simply can't.<br />
<br />
2) Implement two new 6-man levels of play.  One is in between the current "normal" (MOBs hit for 388 to 392) and "hard" (MOBs hit for 988 to 992).<br />
<br />
The second is harder than hard where MOBs hit for 1288 or so.(*)<br />
<br />
3) Change the points. It's fine to keep 51 points for a baseline reward. Heck, I've been in groups where it took 89 minutes to win. But <br />
<br />
105/51 is 2.1<br />
<br />
However, 988 / 388 is 2.5<br />
<br />
The reward for a now "hard" should be closer to 129 points, not 105.<br />
<br />
This would mean that the new "medium" (688 hitters) would be worth 78 points for a succesful run, and the new "hards" would be worth 170 points or so.<br />
<br />
4) Implement a new line of armor and augs.  Where is the MP 4 aug? (for example) Implement a line of armor costing 2100 or so per piece.  Scale it so the base armor is at EP levels.<br />
<br />
5) Change the final reward (Wayfarers Brotherhood Emblem) so that it can be equipped in ANY slot and not just the Charm.  Currently the WBE replaces the Adventurers charm for a whopping net gain of ZERO.<br />
<br />
100 hit points isn't going to break any "down the road" encounters and is a nice "atta boy" for those who complete 366 (MINIMUM) adventures.<br />
<br />
6) Fix Raids.  No I haven't been on one, but neither have I gotten married to a needle-sharing, cross-dressing Haitian prostitute with AIDS.  There are some things that go without saying.<br />
<br />
(*) Note you will have to change pathing and other things or the LDON model. Trial 6 doesn't require you to face up to 4 MOBs at one time, why should an enclosed LDON.<br />
<br />
*************************************************</p>
	
	
	
